<Author>ahs678
<Content>Amazing resort We went to Punta Cana last March and loved it so much we went last week again. I booked through a Canadian airline in September before it opened, knowing is was attached to the #1 resort on the beach. ( Colonial Elegance) The resort exceeded all expectations. When we arrived we got a wrist band that said  Majestic Resorts I asked if that meant we had the run of both resorts, bars, etc. Answer was yes. Not sure if all the guests know this because it isn't advertised and may not last. We could go there, but they couldn't use our resort , at least that was what I was told. So now we had 12 plus bars and the same in restaurants. The room was 1st class .. People on the beach who had been in Punta cana 12x said nicest room to date in Dominican. Very large, LCD tv, huge jaccuzzi, spotless. No issues . Sometimes had to run water 3 minutes to get hot, but always arrived. Those who complain probably didn't do that.Food was excellent. We only ate at the Colonial once, but if it's #1 and you can go there, what's with the complaints. And the food at the Elegance was 1st class anyways, so I would encourage anyone to stay in the resort. Staff is professional and friendly. Only rudeness I saw was from some impatient guests. They should be ashamed of themselves. These people work so hard to accomodate, but as we all know , you can't please everyone.Pool is great but a bit cool They should heat it In March we stayed at another resort and people lived in the pool on foam cushions because it was so comfy.Beach is great, but should cut back on space given to the adult only group. By the way, by going to this area you cut yourself off from the Colonial because you have a band that keeps you only at the Elegance. Apparently it's a separate entity. So you get to be at the ocean with 1/2 the options for more $. If you want adult only, just go to an adult only resort. Personally even though it was a 2 person getaway, I love to watch families enjoy life. To me it's one of the 7 wonders of the world.Goes with the package.So in summary. First class place attached and an extension of #1 resort on the beach , so go figure why it isn't #2. It will be if it isn't #1 in a year or 2. Construction is well done. Stunning lobby and lower plaza. Top notch staff. Great food. Nice fitness center. Would recommend highly. I almost want to apologize to the resort for some early negative reviews, in case they scared people away. Even when I read them I knew to disregard them because it's an extension of the #1 resort in Punta Cana (yeah I know thats repetitive) and it would take a month or 2 to get rolling. Well people, it's rolling.Try it out. 
