<Author>harryliz
<Content>Great Holiday! We just got back yesterday from a week's stay at the Majestic Elegance Resort. There was myself, my partner, my 13 year old son and 10 year old daughter. We were very happy with everything during our stay. The room was luxurious and if you check out the website the pictures are very accurate. Because we were a family of four and I didn't want my kids to stay in a room by themselves we originally booked a room with 2 beds. Our first room had 2 beds but they were only slightly larger than single beds and wouldn't have worked for us. We went back to reception and they were happy to accomodate us. We ended up with a room with a king sized bed which also has a small day bed/couch that my daughter slept on and they provided another single bed which fit in nicely where the couch was. Since there are many families with younger kids it would be a good option for them to have rooms with a king and maybe bunk beds or something similar - the rooms are large and can easily accomodate this set up. That was the only glitch of the week and was quickly resolved. The food at the buffet is plentiful and fresh with lots of choices. The restaurant at the beach also has daily breakfasts and lunches which were both very good. We ate at all the other a la carte restaurants. The steak house was excellent, japanese was fun with great food, italian was our least favourite but still very good. You have to get used to the somewhat slower and less efficient service at the restaurants - it's like that everywhere in the south so just accept it. We saw lots of people complaining about not getting their wine glass filled or their coffee first thing in the morning. Very stressful holiday if this gets you down! We were there over New Year's and went to the buffet for dinner. They went all out with the food - it was amazing!! The pool was fantastic, the beach was beautiful. We had perfect weather. The lobby bar and surrounding area is a great place to play cards, games etc. and they make really good cocktails! My favourite was the cosmopolitan! The entertainment is nightly in the theatre and all nights had great shows. I wanted a relaxing holiday and didn't really leave the resort. I was expecting to get a bit bored but did not at all. A very beautiful resort with lots to do, fantastic food and great service. We had a great trip!***One caution about the beach. . . if you like to walk on the beach there is an area about a 20 minute walk west where the ocean is quite rough. It is directly in front of a huge resort that is currently being built. We went in one day and body surfed the waves which was great fun. My kids went into shore and I followed about 10 minutes after them. By the time I went in the currents had changed drastically. I am a very strong swimmer and used to be a life guard so I know how dangerous water can be. The undertow from the waves was so strong that I could barely stand in 3 ft. of water. I was only a few feet from shore so managed to get in by getting 'surfed' in by the oncoming waves. My partner came in a few minutes after me and is also a very strong swimmer and is very safe. He was trying to swim front crawl toward shore and was being taken out further into the ocean (going backwards!). He eventually did the same as me and surfed himself in. This was only 5-10 minutes after I had come in and the currents changed that quickly. I was very thankful my kids had already gone in. The next day my partner walked along the beach again and in the same spot there was a man on shore that had drowned. The body was still on the shore and there were many police there so it had just happened before he had come upon it. Very, very scary. They should be posting warnings at this area and also informing guests as part of the info that you get when you arrive. 
